      "content": "thanks that helps a bit. but you mentioned it's hard to explain with cause-and-effect. i keep seeing people call it \"spooky action at a distance\" in some of my notes. why do they call it spooky? like is there something actually weird or unpredictable about the way the particles behave, or is it just a metaphor?",
